quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  45,1,"Ha Mim"
  45,2,"This Scripture is sent down from God, the Mighty, the Wise."
  45,3,"There are signs in the heavens and the earth for those who believe:"
  45,4,"in the creation of you, in the creatures God scattered on earth, there are signs for people of sure faith;"
  45,5,"in the alternation of night and day, in the rain God provides, sending it down from the sky and reviving the dead earth with it, and in His shifting of the winds there are signs for those who use their reason."
  45,6,"These are God’s signs that We recount to you [Prophet, to show] the Truth. If they deny God and His revelations, what message will they believe in?"
  45,7,"Woe to every lying sinful person"
  45,8,"who hears God’s revelations being recited to him, yet persists in his arrogance as if he had never heard them––[Prophet] bring him news of a painful torment!––"
  45,9,"who, if he knows anything about Our revelations, ridicules it! Such people will have a humiliating torment:"
  45,10,"Hell lurks behind them and their gains will not benefit them, nor will those beings they took as protectors beside God––a tremendous torment awaits them."